/* MacSift — English strings. The identity mapping is load-bearing:
   SwiftUI's Text("Start Scan") looks up the key "Start Scan" in the
   current locale's Localizable.strings. If the key is missing, SwiftUI
   falls back to displaying the key literally. So leaving this file
   empty technically works in English — but listing the keys here
   explicitly makes the set of localizable strings auditable in one
   place, and catches typos that would otherwise go unnoticed until
   someone switches locale. */

